Question 1-A
a) Modem purpose-
A modem converts digital data into analog signals and vice versa to enable internet communication. Without a modem, direct internet connection is not possible in traditional networks.

b) MAC vs IP Address-
MAC Address: Physical address, fixed, used in LAN
IP Address: Logical address, changeable, used for global communication

c) Loopback IP-
A loopback IP is used to test the network stack.
Range: 127.0.0.0 to 127.255.255.255 (commonly 127.0.0.1)

d) Static IP command (Linux)-
ifconfig eth0 192.168.1.10 netmask 255.255.255.0 up

f) Password strength tool-
Example: zxcvbn or online password checker tools

g) Nmap scan for open ports-
nmap -p- 192.168.1.1


